<!-- ════════ CLOSING ════════ -->
<h2>The Meta-Lesson</h2>

<p>The most important insight from this framework isn't any single step. It's that building LLM agents requires the same engineering discipline as building any complex software system, just with different primitives. You're not training models; you're designing architectures, writing contracts, building guardrails, and instrumenting everything. The teams that treat this as "just prompting" will build demos. The teams that treat it as systems engineering will build products.</p>

<p>The full framework, including formal metric definitions, case studies (personalized multi-turn agents), and an appendix of evaluation metrics, is available in the complete reference document.</p>

